                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d571">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24551U/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Brazzaville (<persName type="to">Taylor</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-21T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 21, 1942—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>111. Department’s 85, August 3, 9 p.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d571fn30">See footnote
                        25, <ref target="#pg_578">p. 578</ref>.</note> War Department has been
                    informed by a member of General Bolte’s staff in London that General Valin, de
                    Gaulle’s Air Chief, has said he fears disagreeable incidents will occur if
                    American aircraft or personnel arrive at Pointe Noire before agreement is
                    reached on Fighting French request for eight liaison aircraft. This may merely
                    be an effort to exert pressure on War Department. Please telegraph immediately
                    whether you consider that such a statement is to be taken seriously.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
